A Load Balancer is a system that distributes incoming user requests across multiple servers to avoid overloading a single server.

Example Real-Time Scenario

Imagine a website like Amazon receiving millions of users.

Without load balancing:

All users hit one server
Server becomes slow or crashes

With load balancing:

Requests are shared among many servers
Website remains fast and available

